<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Ebi on 05-31-2002 01:22 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hello Larians and hello to the other visitors!

(please excuse, there maybe some mistakes in my english, my mother tongue is german. I just thought it would be more polite and more helpful to write in english  ;)   )

I have some additional points, which possibly should be considered in the final version. I don’t know, wether they are mentioned completely before, but unfortunately I’m not able to read the forum as thoroughly as I would like it. And maybe it’s not the worst thing to mention them twice or more to make obvious that they are important.  :)

1.) I miss the possibility to click into the small overview-map to send the character to a point which is more far away as it's shown on the normal screen. That would be extremely useful and I think it for more practicable than other solutions (and it’s approved).

I tried out to hold down the shift-key and move the cursor to select a point afar but it didn't work as relyable as I would wish it. Maybe I’m simply to clumsy?

2.) The already spoken options in the dialogues should be removed. Due to the fact that everyone's able to read the old sentences in the diary this would permit a very fast overview wether there are new dialogue-options or not.

(for example you could still choose the sentence that you'd found a possibility to rescue both soldiers after you had healed them already long time ago).

3.) A right-click into an inventory-window should close this special one.

4.) Left-double-click on a item should generally move it into the inventory and a right-click (or a key in combination with the left-click or a click with the third mousekey) should utilize the item.

The momentary mixture is not optimal (sometimes a left-double-click leads to doing something with the item and another item goes straight to the inventory after double-click with the left mousekey, nobody knows when. And as this wouldn’t be enough, some items have to be drawn to the inventory)

5.) It shouldn’t be allowed to use the teleporting pyramid-stone during a battle! At the moment the healing potions are only usefull to bring money by the trader because I don’t use them. If there are many enemies (or a very strong single one) I use the pyramid-stone to jump directly to my bed, rest for a while and then jump back to the battle, give some hits to the monsters and jump back and so on and so on.
In the momentary constellation he is to mighty.

6.) Special items should be found every time at the same place!! It’s boring to beginn a complete new search after reloading a savegame.

7.) It’s strange when piles of gold are lying on the ground for a longer time (even in the forest). The NPCs should pick them after a while and it should be the same with valuable things, so that the player is forced to use empty barrels or cases (there are enough of them)

8.) The night lasts to long or other way round, the day is to short. That is the connection to the next point.

9.) Daylight should be much stronger (I had always the feeling it’s a rainy day) and in the opposite the night may be a little bit darker. Simple: The difference should be stronger.

10.) Again something with the light: Once you made the effort to stuff all the dungeons with torches or fire basins, why is there still light left, when you douse them?? That’S not logical and a pity about your work with the possibility to influence candles an torches.

11.) Consequently it should be much easier to steal something when it’s dark and the more harder when it’s well lit.


That’s all I remember at the moment. I wish a good game for all of us!! (gamers and developers)

So long
Ebi
</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
